              </div>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-flask mr-2"></i>Polyaniline (PANI)
                  </h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    Most extensively studied CP with straightforward synthesis and exceptional electrochemical properties. Exists in three oxidation states with emeraldine salt form being conductive <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4360/17/17/2346" class="citation" target="_blank">66</a>.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-blue-50 p-3 rounded">
                    <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                      <strong>Performance:</strong> Theoretical capacitance ~2000 F g⁻¹, tunable conductivity from 10⁻⁹ to 100 S/cm
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-ring mr-2"></i>Polypyrrole (PPy)
                  </h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    High electronic conductivity (10⁻³-100 S cm⁻¹) and fast charge transfer kinetics. Based on conjugated pyrrole rings with good affinity for carbon-based substrates <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2227-9717/12/1/31" class="citation" target="_blank">76</a>.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-green-50 p-3 rounded">
                    <p class="text-sm text-green-800">
                      <strong>Challenge:</strong> Lower cycling stability due to mechanical degradation
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-purple-600 mb-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-shield-alt mr-2"></i>PEDOT:PSS
                  </h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    Leading conductive polymer with exceptional stability, high conductivity (&gt;1000 S/cm), and water dispersibility for easy fabrication <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4360/17/17/2346" class="citation" target="_blank">66</a>.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-purple-50 p-3 rounded">
                    <p class="text-sm text-purple-800">
                      <strong>Advantage:</strong> Minimal structural disruption during redox process
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-3">
                  <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle mr-2"></i>Common Challenge: Cycling Stability
                </h4>
                <p class="text-yellow-700">
                  A major drawback of many conductive polymers is their <strong>poor long-term cycling stability</strong>. The repeated swelling and shrinking of the polymer matrix during ion insertion/extraction can lead to mechanical degradation and gradual capacitance decline <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8151924/" class="citation" target="_blank">60</a>.
                </p>
                <p class="text-yellow-700 mt-3">
                  <strong>Solutions:</strong> Creating nanostructured polymers, forming composites with carbon materials, and designing novel polymer architectures to enhance mechanical integrity.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

