      <!-- Electrolytes Section -->
      <section id="electrolytes" class="py-16 px-8 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          <h2 class="serif-heading text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Core Components: Electrolytes and Ion Transport</h2>

          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              The electrolyte is a critical component in a supercapacitor, serving as the medium for ion transport between the positive and negative electrodes. Its properties, including <strong>ionic conductivity, electrochemical stability, viscosity, and operating temperature range</strong>, profoundly influence the overall performance of the device <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11582294/" class="citation" target="_blank">173</a>.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-blue-600">
                <i class="fas fa-tint mr-3"></i>Aqueous Electrolytes
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Water-based electrolytes with exceptionally high ionic conductivity (up to 800 mS/cm) and low cost. Common examples include H₂SO₄, KOH, and Na₂SO₄ solutions <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s42247-025-01284-5" class="citation" target="_blank">160</a>.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-3 rounded">
                  <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                    <strong>Advantage:</strong> High ionic conductivity, low cost, non-flammable
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-red-50 p-3 rounded">
                  <p class="text-sm text-red-800">
                    <strong>Limitation:</strong> Narrow voltage window (~1.2V), corrosive nature
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-green-50 rounded">
                <p class="text-sm text-green-800">
                  <strong>Innovation:</strong> Zn²⁺-driven cellulose hydrogel extends voltage window to <strong>2V</strong> by inhibiting water electrolysis <a href="https://figshare.com/collections/A_High-Voltage_Supercapacitor_Electrolyte_Based_on_Zn_sup_2_sup_-Driven_Self-Adhesive_Cellulose_Hydrogel/7841958" class="citation" target="_blank">164</a>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-green-600">
                <i class="fas fa-flask mr-3"></i>Organic Electrolytes
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Most common in commercial supercapacitors, using solvents like acetonitrile (AN) or propylene carbonate (PC) with salts such as TEABF₄. Key advantage is wider electrochemical stability window <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s42247-025-01284-5" class="citation" target="_blank">160</a>.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="bg-green-50 p-3 rounded">
                  <p class="text-sm text-green-800">
                    <strong>Advantage:</strong> Wide voltage window (2.7-3.0V), high energy density
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-3 rounded">
                  <p class="text-sm text-yellow-800">
                    <strong>Drawbacks:</strong> Lower conductivity, flammability concerns, higher cost
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-blue-50 rounded">
                <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                  <strong>Performance:</strong> AN-based electrolyte shows excellent stability, retaining over <strong>95% capacity after 100,000 cycles</strong> at 2.7V <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s42247-025-01284-5" class="citation" target="_blank">160</a>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-purple-600">
                <i class="fas fa-atom mr-3"></i>Ionic Liquids (ILs)
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Salts that are liquid at room temperature, offering exceptional properties for next-generation supercapacitors. Composed entirely of ions with very wide electrochemical stability window <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s42247-025-01284-5" class="citation" target="_blank">160</a>.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="bg-purple-50 p-3 rounded">
                  <p class="text-sm text-purple-800">
                    <strong>Benefits:</strong> Very wide window (3.5-4.0V), high thermal stability, non-flammable
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-red-50 p-3 rounded">
                  <p class="text-sm text-red-800">
                    <strong>Challenges:</strong> High viscosity (70 mPa·s), high cost (&gt; $500/kg)
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-green-50 rounded">
                <p class="text-sm text-green-800">
                  <strong>Potential:</strong> EMIM-TFSI ionic liquid enables energy densities <strong>exceeding 50 Wh/kg</strong>, representing substantial improvement over conventional systems <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s42247-025-01284-5" class="citation" target="_blank">160</a>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-indigo-600">
                <i class="fas fa-cube mr-3"></i>Solid-State Electrolytes
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Represent significant advancement offering enhanced safety, flexibility, and mechanical robustness. Eliminate risks of leakage, evaporation, and flammability associated with liquid systems <a href="https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/acsapm.5c02845" class="citation" target="_blank">161</a>.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-3 rounded">
