      <section id="performance" class="py-16 px-8">
        <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          <h2 class="serif-heading text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Performance Metrics and Characterization</h2>

          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              The performance of a supercapacitor is evaluated using a set of key performance indicators (KPIs) that quantify its energy storage and delivery capabilities. These metrics are essential for comparing different supercapacitor technologies and for selecting the most appropriate device for specific applications.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-blue-600">
                <i class="fas fa-battery-half mr-3"></i>Key Performance Indicators
              </h3>

              <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Capacitance</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">
                    Measure of charge storage ability, typically expressed as specific capacitance (F/g) for material comparison or areal capacitance (F/cm²) for footprint considerations.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-blue-50 p-2 rounded">
                    <p class="text-xs text-blue-700">
                      <strong>Measurement:</strong> Cyclic voltammetry (CV) and galvanostatic charge-discharge (GCD)
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Energy &amp; Power Density</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">
                    Energy density (Wh/kg or Wh/L) measures total energy storage, while power density (W/kg or W/L) measures energy delivery rate.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-green-50 p-2 rounded">
                    <p class="text-xs text-green-700">
                      <strong>Relationship:</strong> E = ½CV² for energy density
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Cycle Life &amp; Stability</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">
                    Number of charge-discharge cycles before performance degrades to specified level (typically 80% of initial capacitance).
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-purple-50 p-2 rounded">
                    <p class="text-xs text-purple-700">
                      <strong>Supercapacitor Advantage:</strong> Hundreds of thousands to millions of cycles
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-green-600">
                <i class="fas fa-microscope mr-3"></i>Characterization Techniques
              </h3>

              <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Cyclic Voltammetry (CV)</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">
                    Powerful technique where voltage is swept at constant rate while measuring current. Provides information about charge storage mechanism and capacitance.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-blue-50 p-2 rounded">
                    <p class="text-xs text-blue-700">
                      <strong>EDLC:</strong> Rectangular curve
                      <br/>
                      <strong>Pseudocapacitor:</strong> Peaks indicating redox reactions
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Galvanostatic Charge-Discharge (GCD)</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">
                    Device charged and discharged at constant current while measuring voltage vs. time. Determines capacitance, energy, and power density.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-green-50 p-2 rounded">
                    <p class="text-xs text-green-700">
                      <strong>EDLC:</strong> Straight line voltage profile
                      <br/>
                      <strong>Pseudocapacitor:</strong> Plateaus during redox reactions
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy (EIS)</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">
                    Small sinusoidal voltage applied across frequency range to study internal resistance and ion diffusion kinetics.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-purple-50 p-2 rounded">
                    <p class="text-xs text-purple-700">
                      <strong>Key Output:</strong> Nyquist plot showing equivalent series resistance (ESR)
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-4">
              <i class="fas fa-trophy mr-2"></i>Performance Benchmarks
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-2">Commercial EDLCs</h4>
