      <section id="challenges" class="py-16 px-8">
        <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          <h2 class="serif-heading text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Advantages, Limitations, and System Integration Challenges</h2>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-green-600">
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle mr-3"></i>Key Advantages
              </h3>

              <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">High Power Density &amp; Fast Charge/Discharge</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                    Exceptionally high power density (several orders of magnitude greater than batteries) enables rapid energy delivery and absorption. Charge and discharge in seconds or minutes compared to hours for batteries <a href="https://www.scirp.org/journal/paperinformation?paperid=143807" class="citation" target="_blank">166</a>.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Long Cycle Life &amp; High Reliability</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                    Can withstand hundreds of thousands to millions of charge-discharge cycles with minimal degradation due to physical energy storage mechanism <a href="https://commons.und.edu/theses/7120/" class="citation" target="_blank">144</a>.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Wide Operating Temperature Range</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                    Capable of operating from -40°C to +65°C, making them suitable for automotive, aerospace, and industrial applications where extreme temperatures are common <a href="https://commons.und.edu/theses/7120/" class="citation" target="_blank">144</a>.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="mt-6 bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-green-800">
                  <strong>Additional Benefits:</strong> Low maintenance requirements, high reliability, resistance to shock and vibration, and environmentally friendly materials in many configurations.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
              <h3 class="serif-heading text-xl font-semibold mb-6 text-red-600">
                <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle mr-3"></i>Key Limitations
              </h3>

              <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Lower Energy Density Compared to Batteries</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                    Typical energy density of 5-20 Wh/kg is 20-40 times lower than lithium-ion batteries (100-265 Wh/kg), limiting use in applications requiring prolonged energy delivery <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1226086X24004593" class="citation" target="_blank">252</a>.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">High Initial Cost</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                    Manufacturing complexity and specialized materials contribute to higher upfront investment compared to traditional energy storage solutions. Activated carbon cost needs to drop below $10/kg for true economic viability <a href="https://www.energy.gov/sites/default/files/2024-02/10_Technology%20Strategy%20Assessment%20-%20%2310%20Supercapacitors_508_rev.pdf" class="citation" target="_blank">238</a>.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-yellow-500 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Self-Discharge and Voltage Drop</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                    Relatively high self-discharge rate due to leakage currents, and linear voltage drop during discharge may require voltage regulation for stable output applications.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

